`--add-opens=java.base/java.lang=ALL-UNNAMED`. I should explore running a temporary Gradle project that utilizes the necessary dependencies like JUnit to avoid modifying the repository.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring minimal Java setup**\\n\\nI'm considering trying a minimal setup with Java, probably using JDK 21 instead of 25, as there may be security issues with the latter. I'm also wondering if the setup goes beyond the scaffold. I’ll check the documentation; it seems that using simple expressions shouldn't require any extras. Artifact and transitive dependencies can manage Javassist without needing a server. There are optional system properties, but they don't seem to be necessary for this setup.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Inspecting JVM properties**\\n\\nI'm looking at the setup, which can involve env/system properties and JVM arguments like \\\"add-opens.\\\" It seems that the existing scaffold already includes some `jvmArgs`. The version 3.3.5 is probably something I should keep as a target. I wonder if I don't need to cover \\\"before meaningful coverage,\\\" especially with OGNL's existing coverage. I think it would be helpful to check the Ognl 3.3.5 source for any errors related to the JDK9 handler.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Vin7VKuq9tzi8fJ3Qbah8hKI|fc_0fc2d8ad49212b3e016a421dd84c908196895a7bc9c6d92631", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "tmp=$(mktemp -d); cd \"$tmp\" && curl -fsSLO https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/ognl/ognl/3.3.5/ognl-3.3.5-sources.jar && jar xf ognl-3.3.5-sources.jar && grep -R \"setAccessible\\|AccessibleObjectHandler\" -n ognl | head -80", "timeout": 30}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2778, "output": 930, "cacheRead": 32256, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 35964, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782717893632, "responseId": "res